Responsibility:
1. AGF onsite deployment, debugging, troubleshooting and customer training in overseas project;
2. AGF operational status tracking, recording and summarizing in overseas project onsite, and regularly reporting to project manager;
3. Responsible for project documentations;
4. After-sales repair and maintenance;
5. Develop and follow up project schedule plan for overseas projects, communication and coordinate with customers for technical problems;
6. Timely feedback customer requirement, constantly improve project management skills and improve customer service level;
7. Complete other tasks assigned by the manager;

Requirements:
1. Associate degree or above, major in electrical engineering, automation, electronic engineering or related;
2. Familiar with CAD, SolidWorks, Excel, Word, PPT and other office software;
3. Good learning ability;
4. Cantonese and Mandarin are main working languages, good communication skills is preferred
5. Enthusiastic in work, strong adaptability and stress resistance, good teamwork spirit and customer service awareness, able to travel
6. Having experience in electrical automation industry and FAE work experience is preferred;
7. Having experience in AGV, AGF or forklift maintenance is preferred.

Corporate member of a professional institution recognized for corporate membership in the status of registered professional engineer (RPE) of the Hong Kong Institution of Engineers (HKIE) in the Building Services Engineering or Electrical Engineering or Mechanical Engineering Discipline, or equivalent;
At least 5 years relevant post qualification experience in building services engineering, electrical engineering or mechanical engineering;
Work on construction site.

We offer competitive salary package and career development opportunity to the successful candidate. Interested parties may send your full resume, present and expected salary, available date and contact number by email by clicking "Apply Now".


To visit our website for more information: www.ableeng.com.hk

